==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[ceorfan|ċeorfan]], from West Germanic ''*kerfan''.  Cognate with Dutch [[kerven]], and perhaps ultimately with Greek [[γράφειν]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/kɑ:v/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb2|'''carve'''|'''[[carves]]'''|'''[[carved]]'''|'''[[carved]]''', or archaic '''[[carven]]'''|'''[[carving]]'''}}

# ''(archaic)'' To [[cut]].
# To cut meat in order to serve it.
# To shape wood to sculptural effect.
# {{snowboarding}}: To perform a series of turns without pivotting. When the tip and tail of the snowboard take the same path.

